WEBVTT

00:03.637 --> 00:07.673
Jimmy: WHAT WOULD YOU DO
WITH A SECOND CHANCE?

00:07.675 --> 00:11.710
BEFORE YOU ANSWER,
LET ME GIVE YOU SOME ADVICE.

00:11.712 --> 00:15.381
SECOND CHANCES CAN BE
A REAL MONSTER.

00:20.855 --> 00:23.722
[ CREEDENCE CLEARWATER REVIVAL'S
"BAD MOON RISING" PLAYS ]

00:24.558 --> 00:25.991
I'M GONNA CALL
THE POLICE.

00:25.993 --> 00:27.826
NO NEED FOR THAT.
¶ I SEE A BAD MOON RISING ¶

00:27.828 --> 00:29.328
THAT SAME MUSIC
OVER AND OVER.

00:29.330 --> 00:30.896
I'M GONNA GET THE COPS
UP HERE.

00:30.898 --> 00:33.298
FBI. WILL THAT DO?

00:33.300 --> 00:36.502
¶ I SEE TROUBLE ON THE WAY ¶

00:36.504 --> 00:37.970
¶ I SEE EARTHQUAKES
AND LIGHTNIN' ¶

00:37.972 --> 00:40.372
NEIGHBORS ARE COMPLAINING
ABOUT THE NOISE AGAIN, DAD.

00:42.243 --> 00:43.609
¶ I SEE ¶

00:46.180 --> 00:50.315
WHY DON'T YOU GO AHEAD
AND LET ME HAVE THAT SMOKE, TOO?

00:50.317 --> 00:52.885
COME ON.

00:52.887 --> 00:55.754
I WAS HAVING A LOT MORE FUN
BEFORE YOU SHOWED UP.

00:55.756 --> 00:56.922
IT'S 3:00 IN THE AFTERNOON.

00:56.924 --> 00:58.657
ARE YOU PLANNING ON
GETTING DRESSED TODAY?

00:58.659 --> 01:00.993
I WILL TAKE IT
UNDER ADVISEMENT.

01:03.030 --> 01:05.497
WHAT'S ALL THIS?

01:05.499 --> 01:07.266
IS THIS MY CASE?

01:07.268 --> 01:09.001
YOU'RE WORKING MY CASE NOW?

01:09.003 --> 01:11.036
[ CHUCKLES ]
SOMEONE HAS TO.

01:11.038 --> 01:13.105
SIX BANK JOBS IN 12 MONTHS,

01:13.107 --> 01:16.675
DEAD SECURITY GUARD,
NOBODY LOCKED UP FOR IT.

01:16.677 --> 01:18.510
[ CHUCKLES ] IN MY DAY,
WE WOULD'VE DONE --

01:18.512 --> 01:19.578
WHAT NEEDED TO GET DONE.

01:19.580 --> 01:21.246
YEAH, I'M PRETTY MUCH
AWARE OF THAT.

01:21.248 --> 01:22.681
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]

01:22.683 --> 01:23.549
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

01:23.551 --> 01:25.350
DAD, IS SOMEBODY ELSE HERE?

01:25.352 --> 01:27.219
OH. HEY.

01:27.221 --> 01:28.420
I WAS JUST ON MY WAY OUT.

01:28.422 --> 01:30.456
DUVAL, THIS IS BETTINA.

01:30.458 --> 01:34.626
BETTINA IS A MEMBER OF MY,
UH, MUSIC APPRECIATION CLUB.

01:34.628 --> 01:37.362
WE MEET ONCE A WEEK.

01:37.364 --> 01:38.797
DON'T WORRY.

01:38.799 --> 01:40.966
HE'S TOO OLD TO REALLY
DO MUCH OF ANYTHING.

01:40.968 --> 01:43.802
AND HOW MUCH DOES NOT REALLY
DOING MUCH OF ANYTHING COST HIM?

01:43.804 --> 01:45.070
DON'T ANSWER THAT!

01:45.072 --> 01:46.738
IT'S IMPOLITE
TO TALK ABOUT MONEY.

01:46.740 --> 01:47.973
MY SON SHOULD KNOW THAT.

01:47.975 --> 01:50.075
DON'T BE RUDE, DUVAL.

01:50.077 --> 01:53.212
I'LL SEE YOU.
YOU KNOW WHERE TO FIND ME.

01:54.982 --> 01:56.215
OH! HELLO.

01:56.217 --> 01:57.316
HELLO.
OH, GEEZ.

01:57.318 --> 01:59.651
ARE YOU HERE FOR
THE MUSIC APPRECIATION CLUB?

01:59.653 --> 02:01.553
THE MUSIC...I'M SORRY.
THE WHAT CLUB?

02:01.555 --> 02:03.655
GRACIE, I THOUGHT I TOLD YOU
TO WAIT IN THE CAR.

02:03.657 --> 02:04.890
WELL, I WANTED TO COME
SAY HI TO GRANDPA.

02:04.892 --> 02:07.126
I'LL SEE YOU NEXT WEEK.

02:07.128 --> 02:08.260
WHO WAS THAT?

02:08.262 --> 02:10.629
NO ONE. GRACIE,
AS LONG AS YOU'RE HERE,

02:10.631 --> 02:13.132
GO AHEAD AND EMPTY
THE REST OF THAT BOURBON

02:13.134 --> 02:14.566
IN THE KITCHEN SINK.

02:14.568 --> 02:16.268
GRANDPA, WHAT DOES THE DOCTOR
SAY ABOUT MIXING YOUR MEDS

02:16.270 --> 02:17.302
AND BOURBON?

02:17.304 --> 02:19.605
OH, THAT I HAD TO
GIVE ONE OF THEM UP.

02:19.607 --> 02:21.140
CAN'T REMEMBER WHICH ONE.

02:21.142 --> 02:24.276
OH, YOU KNOW, I USED TO
HAVE A LOT MORE RECORDS.

02:24.278 --> 02:25.644
YOU KNOW WHAT
HAPPENED TO THEM?

02:25.646 --> 02:27.646
YEAH, THEY'RE WITH THE BOXES
FROM WHEN WE SHUT DOWN

02:27.648 --> 02:29.615
YOUR HOUSE --
AFTER MOM DIED.

02:29.617 --> 02:30.282
AH.

02:30.284 --> 02:31.350
THEY'RE UP IN OUR ATTIC.

02:31.352 --> 02:32.851
I CAN GO UP THERE
WHEN WE GET BACK.

02:32.853 --> 02:35.654
REMEMBER? DAD'S TAKING ME
ON A COLLEGE GRACIE TOUR.

02:35.656 --> 02:36.822
YOU CAN TAKE THE TIME?

02:36.824 --> 02:38.824
IT'S TWO DAYS
WITH MY DAUGHTER.

02:38.826 --> 02:41.093
I'VE BEEN ON THIS CASE
FOR A YEAR.

02:41.095 --> 02:42.728
YOU KNOW BEST.
KIDDO.

02:44.465 --> 02:46.331
GRACIE, COME ON, LET'S GO.
OKAY.

02:48.135 --> 02:49.835
I, UH, I POURED A LITTLE
OF THE BOURBON

02:49.837 --> 02:50.936
INTO A GLASS BY THE SINK.

02:50.938 --> 02:52.471
OH, YOU ARE
AN UNDERSTANDING CHILD.

02:52.473 --> 02:54.439
GRACIE?

02:54.441 --> 02:56.608
YOU'LL ALWAYS BE THE SHERIFF.

02:56.610 --> 02:57.643
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:57.645 --> 02:59.845
DON'T LET YOUR FATHER
HEAR YOU SAY THAT.

02:59.847 --> 03:00.946
HE DOESN'T LIKE IT.

03:00.948 --> 03:03.081
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

03:05.286 --> 03:08.153
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

03:08.155 --> 03:11.123
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:16.497 --> 03:20.666
¶ EVERY DAY,
YOU WAKE UP IN THE MORNING ¶

03:20.668 --> 03:24.836
¶ TRYING TO IGNORE
THE WAY YOU FEEL ¶

03:24.838 --> 03:27.806
¶ READING ALL THE BAD NEWS
IN THE PAPERS ¶

03:27.808 --> 03:32.844
¶ OF ALL THE PEOPLE THAT
ARE SLEEPING AT THE WHEEL ¶

03:32.846 --> 03:36.848
¶ CAN'T BELIEVE A THING
YOUR DADDY TOLD YA ¶

03:36.850 --> 03:40.986
¶ COULDN'T EVER EVEN
WALK A LINE ¶

03:40.988 --> 03:44.923
¶ MAMA ALWAYS HAD
HER BEST INTENTIONS ¶

03:44.925 --> 03:46.825
¶ TELLING YOU EVERYTHING
WILL BE FINE ¶

03:46.827 --> 03:48.994
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT FACE THAT IS.

03:48.996 --> 03:50.729
IT'S MY REASSURING FACE,
OTTO.

03:50.731 --> 03:51.730
OH.

03:51.732 --> 03:53.498
I THOUGHT MAYBE
IT WAS ANXIOUS.

03:53.500 --> 03:54.766
MAYBE IT'S A BIT OF BOTH.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.668
THE BOARD NEEDS ME
TO DO INTERVIEWS

03:56.670 --> 03:58.170
TO EASE
THE SHAREHOLDERS' MINDS.

03:58.172 --> 04:01.607
THEY'LL ASK WHAT
YOU'VE BEEN DOING, OTTO.

04:01.609 --> 04:03.375
[ SPEAKING TWIN-SPEAK ]

04:03.377 --> 04:06.511
NOT IN TWIN-SPEAK, OTTO.
IN ENGLISH.

04:06.513 --> 04:08.013
YOU WON'T TELL THEM,
WILL YOU?

04:08.015 --> 04:10.349
NO.

04:10.351 --> 04:11.783
I WON'T TELL THEM.

04:13.754 --> 04:17.122
IT WORKS WITH THE FISH.
I WANT TO GO TO HUMAN TRIALS.

04:17.124 --> 04:20.425
AFTER MICE, RATS, AND CHIMPS.
YOU KNOW THAT, OTTO.

04:20.427 --> 04:21.727
BUT WE CAN'T WAIT.

04:21.729 --> 04:23.795
YOU'RE TOO SICK, MARY.

04:23.797 --> 04:29.134
THEY WERE DEAD.

04:29.136 --> 04:30.369
WE BROUGHT THEM BACK.

04:30.371 --> 04:33.972
¶ SO, DON'T CLOSE YOUR EYES ¶

04:33.974 --> 04:37.809
¶ OR TIME WILL PASS YOU BY ¶

04:37.811 --> 04:39.111
¶ OH, OH ¶

04:39.113 --> 04:42.914
¶ DON'T HEAR, DON'T SEE,
DON'T SPEAK NO EVIL ¶

04:42.916 --> 04:46.818
¶ DON'T HEAR, DON'T SEE,
DON'T SPEAK NO EVIL ¶

04:46.820 --> 04:49.488
¶ DON'T HEAR, DON'T SEE,
DON'T SPEAK NO EVIL ¶

04:49.490 --> 04:53.892
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

05:08.008 --> 05:10.142
[ CREAKING ]

05:12.246 --> 05:15.047
¶¶

05:30.931 --> 05:32.431
[ PAPER RIPS ]

05:32.433 --> 05:34.866
Jimmy: WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
DOING IN MY SON'S OFFICE?!

05:34.868 --> 05:35.934
JUST TAKE IT EASY.

05:35.936 --> 05:37.302
I ASKED YOU A QUESTION.

05:37.304 --> 05:38.303
ANSWER ME!

05:38.305 --> 05:39.371
LOOK ME IN THE EYE!

05:39.373 --> 05:41.273
OR WE WILL BOTH FIND OUT
IF I REMEMBER

05:41.275 --> 05:43.041
HOW TO THROW THIS KNIFE.

05:43.043 --> 05:44.643
NO, DON'T DO IT!

05:44.645 --> 05:46.111
UNH!

05:46.113 --> 05:48.680
[ GROANS ]

05:48.682 --> 05:51.450
Man: GET WHAT WE NEED.

05:51.452 --> 05:53.485
CLEAN THIS PLACE UP
LIKE IT NEVER HAPPENED.

05:53.487 --> 05:55.787
GO TO HELL!

06:01.061 --> 06:03.562
I GOT A BETTER IDEA,
SHERIFF.

06:06.166 --> 06:11.169
YOU WERE DEPRESSED,
DRINKING TOO MUCH.

06:11.171 --> 06:12.204
[ GRUNTS ]

06:12.206 --> 06:13.872
AFTER WHAT YOU PUT
YOUR FAMILY THROUGH.

06:13.874 --> 06:15.674
[ COUGHS ]

06:15.676 --> 06:17.743
I'M SURPRISED IT TOOK YOU
SO LONG TO DO IT.

06:19.012 --> 06:20.979
ALL RIGHT, GET HIM OVER!

06:20.981 --> 06:21.680
WHAT?

06:21.682 --> 06:22.481
DO IT!

06:22.483 --> 06:23.815
HE'S SEEN OUR FACES!

06:23.817 --> 06:25.584
COME ON, MAN, DO IT NOW!

06:25.586 --> 06:27.519
MY SON WILL CATCH YOU!

06:27.521 --> 06:29.888
NO, MR. PRITCHARD,
HE WON'T.

06:32.259 --> 06:34.326
[ GASPS ]

06:36.497 --> 06:38.463
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

06:41.101 --> 06:42.401
[ GUNS COCK ]

06:46.006 --> 06:48.373
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

06:48.375 --> 06:50.175
<i> Reporter: IN WHAT IS BEING</i>
<i> RULED</i>
A SUICIDE,

06:50.177 --> 06:52.778
<i> EX-KING COUNTY SHERIFF</i>
<i> JIMMY PRITCHARD</i>

06:52.780 --> 06:55.113
<i> TOOK HIS OWN LIFE</i>
<i> NEARLY 15 YEARS</i>

06:55.115 --> 06:57.048
<i> AFTER STEPPING DOWN</i>
<i> FROM HIS OFFICE</i>

06:57.050 --> 07:00.185
<i> IN THE WAKE OF A WIDESPREAD</i>
<i> CORRUPTION SCANDAL.</i>

07:00.187 --> 07:03.688
<i> PRITCHARD IS SURVIVED BY TWO</i>
<i> CHILDREN AND ONE GRANDCHILD.</i>

07:05.259 --> 07:07.092
[ BEEP ]

07:07.094 --> 07:09.361
4-YEAR-OLD OTTO GOODWIN,

07:09.363 --> 07:11.630
UNABLE TO CONNECT WITH
THE WORLD AROUND HIM,

07:11.632 --> 07:15.634
CONSTRUCTED A PRIVATE LANGUAGE
CONSISTING OF OVER 3,000 WORDS.

07:15.636 --> 07:18.737
HIS TWIN SISTER, MARY, WAS
THE ONLY PERSON HE TAUGHT IT TO.

07:18.739 --> 07:22.140
HE WOULD SPEAK TO HER.
SHE WOULD SPEAK TO THE WORLD.

07:22.142 --> 07:25.043
WITHIN A FEW YEARS,
HE WOULD GIVE MARY THE ALGORITHM

07:25.045 --> 07:27.779
FOR LOOKING GLASS,
AND SHE WOULD TURN IT INTO

07:27.781 --> 07:30.615
A $10-BILLION
SOCIAL-MEDIA GIANT.

07:30.617 --> 07:32.317
Morgan: MARY, WHEN YOU
AND YOUR TWIN BROTHER

07:32.319 --> 07:34.085
STARTED LOOKING GLASS
NEARLY 10 YEARS AGO NOW,

07:34.087 --> 07:37.722
DID YOU EVER IMAGINE YOU'D
END UP WITH A BILLION USERS?

07:37.724 --> 07:39.758
OTTO WROTE THAT CODE TO
HELP PEOPLE CONNECT.

07:39.760 --> 07:42.227
THAT NUMBER ONE BILLION
SHOWS HOW HUNGRY PEOPLE ARE

07:42.229 --> 07:43.495
TO CONNECT WITH EACH OTHER.

07:43.497 --> 07:46.131
BUT HUMAN CONNECTION
IS SOMETHING THAT OTTO

07:46.133 --> 07:47.966
HAS ALWAYS STRUGGLED WITH,

07:47.968 --> 07:51.069
AND HE SPOKE ONLY TO YOU
TILL HE WAS 9 YEARS OLD

07:51.071 --> 07:54.139
AND THEN ONLY THE LANGUAGE
OF HIS OWN INVENTION.

07:54.141 --> 07:56.074
AND PEOPLE ARE SAYING
TWO THINGS.

07:56.076 --> 07:59.778
<i> I WANT TO PUT THESE TO YOU</i>
<i> VERY STRONGLY TONIGHT.</i>

07:59.780 --> 08:00.979
<i> THE OBVIOUS QUESTION</i>
<i> FOR YOU...</i>

08:00.981 --> 08:02.514
Otto: COME ON, MARY.
<i> ...IS OTTO BURNT OUT?</i>

08:02.516 --> 08:04.316
SAY YES.
<i> CAN LOOKING GLASS SURVIVE</i>
<i> WITHOUT HIM?</i>

08:04.318 --> 08:05.484
SAY YES.

08:05.486 --> 08:07.319
OTTO'S BECOME VERY DISTANT,

08:07.321 --> 08:09.454
ALMOST DISAPPEARED
OFF THE FACE OF THE EARTH,

08:09.456 --> 08:13.158
<i> AND HIS ABSENCE HAS CREATED</i>
<i> A VACUUM WHERE COMPETITORS</i>

08:13.160 --> 08:14.192
<i> CAN POUNCE INTO THE MARKET.</i>

08:14.194 --> 08:16.862
<i> I'M SORRY, OTTO.</i>
<i> MARY SAYS NO.</i>

08:16.864 --> 08:21.266
WHY? DOESN'T SHE KNOW THAT BY
THE TIME WE FIND ANOTHER DONOR,

08:21.268 --> 08:23.201
IT'LL BE TOO LATE?
WHY WOULD SHE SAY NO?!

08:23.203 --> 08:24.803
<i> YOU KNOW WHY, OTTO.</i>

08:24.805 --> 08:27.973
<i> YOUR SISTER STILL HASN'T GIVEN</i>
<i>THE GO AHEAD FOR HUMAN TESTING.</i>

08:27.975 --> 08:30.308
BUT IT'S THE ONLY THING
THAT'LL SAVE HER!

08:30.310 --> 08:33.111
<i> ...A LOT OF WAITING.</i>

08:33.113 --> 08:35.981
ARTHUR, HOW LONG WILL MARY
BE IN NEW YORK?

08:35.983 --> 08:37.983
<i> SHE HAS ONE MORE DAY</i>
<i> OF INTERVIEWS.</i>

08:37.985 --> 08:39.451
OKAY.

08:39.453 --> 08:41.953
<i> HE'S ESSENTIALLY</i>
<i> JUST DISAPPEARED.</i>

08:41.955 --> 08:42.654
OKAY.

08:42.656 --> 08:43.889
<i> MOST CONCERNING...</i>

08:43.891 --> 08:48.460
SWITCH THE SERIAL NUMBERS.
PROCURE THE BODY.

08:48.462 --> 08:51.229
<i> SHE IS GOING TO BE ANGRY.</i>
<i> YOU KNOW THAT.</i>

08:51.231 --> 08:53.365
¶¶

08:56.203 --> 08:58.303
[ BEEPING ]

09:01.542 --> 09:03.074
[ BEEP ]

09:03.076 --> 09:04.175
[ PING ]

09:04.177 --> 09:06.912
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

09:15.989 --> 09:17.822
WHAT DID YOU DO, OTTO?

09:17.824 --> 09:18.857
PLEASE DON'T BE MAD.

09:18.859 --> 09:20.492
ARTHUR,
TERMINATE THE PROCESS!

09:20.494 --> 09:23.328
TURN IT OFF!
TURN IT ALL OFF NOW!

09:23.330 --> 09:25.063
<i> Arthur: YES, MARY.</i>
<i> GIVE ME A MOMENT.</i>

09:25.065 --> 09:26.164
PLEASE, MARY, DON'T.

09:26.166 --> 09:27.732
WE HAD NO RIGHT
TO DO THIS --

09:27.734 --> 09:29.534
TO TAKE A BODY
WITHOUT ASKING!

09:29.536 --> 09:31.269
<i> SHUTTING DOWN IN 25 SECONDS.</i>

09:31.271 --> 09:32.537
PLEASE, MARY, DON'T!

09:32.539 --> 09:34.773
WE NEED TO SEND HIM BACK.
HE SHOULDN'T BE HERE!

09:34.775 --> 09:36.841
PLEASE, LET ME JUST TELL YOU
WHO HE IS FIRST.

09:36.843 --> 09:39.177
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

09:39.179 --> 09:41.246
IT'S WHO WE'VE BEEN
WAITING FOR.

09:41.248 --> 09:43.949
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

09:43.951 --> 09:46.184
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DIE,
MARY.

09:46.186 --> 09:49.955
HIS GENETIC VARIATION
IS 1 IN 10 MILLION.

09:49.957 --> 09:53.124
<i> 15 SECONDS.</i>

09:53.126 --> 09:56.895
IT WORKS WITH HIM, MARY.

09:56.897 --> 10:01.866
HE'S HERE TO SAVE US.

10:01.868 --> 10:04.169
PLEASE DON'T
LEAVE ME ALONE.

10:05.806 --> 10:11.643
MY FATHER, JIMMY PRITCHARD, WAS
IN THE DEPARTMENT FOR 30 YEARS,

10:11.645 --> 10:13.378
AND...

10:13.380 --> 10:15.914
THEY DIDN'T EVEN SEND
A COUPLE OF LOUSY MOTORCYCLES.

10:15.916 --> 10:20.752
WITHOUT DEPARTMENTAL HONORS.

10:20.754 --> 10:23.755
HE DIDN'T EXPECT
ANYTHING OF ANYONE.

10:23.757 --> 10:25.590
DIDN'T EXPECT ANYTHING OF ME.

10:25.592 --> 10:26.891
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S --
THAT'S ENOUGH NOW, HELEN.

10:26.893 --> 10:27.826
MM!

10:27.828 --> 10:29.828
YOU'VE HAD TOO MUCH
TO DRINK.

10:29.830 --> 10:30.929
OH! [ LAUGHS ]

10:30.931 --> 10:32.998
WELL, IT'S THE ONLY THING
HE TAUGHT ME.

10:33.000 --> 10:34.499
MEET ME IN MY OFFICE.

10:41.742 --> 10:43.775
[ CABINET CLOSES ]

10:43.777 --> 10:46.411
YOU REMEMBER THE GUARD
THEY KILLED ON THE FIRST JOB?

10:46.413 --> 10:48.480
YOU'VE GOT TO BE
KIDDING ME, PARTNER.
WE'RE NOT WORKING TODAY.

10:48.482 --> 10:50.649
I GOT TO THINKING,
MAYBE HE WAS IN ON IT,

10:50.651 --> 10:53.318
AND THEY WERE CLEANING UP
WHEN THEY KILLED HIM.

10:53.320 --> 10:54.986
SO I PULLED
HIS PHONE RECORDS.

10:54.988 --> 10:58.490
OKAY.
PULLED HIS PHONE RECORDS, AND...

10:58.492 --> 11:01.326
NOTHING CONNECTS HIM TO IT.

11:01.328 --> 11:03.628
WHY CAN'T WE GET
THESE GUYS?

11:03.630 --> 11:05.130
DUVAL,
THAT'S FOR TOMORROW.

11:05.132 --> 11:08.033
TODAY'S ABOUT YOUR FAMILY,
YOUR DAD.

11:08.035 --> 11:11.670
MY DAD WOULD'VE WANTED ME
TO WORK TODAY, BELIEVE ME.

11:22.482 --> 11:25.617
HIS CELLS, RECODED FOR
OPTIMUM GROWTH AND CAPACITY,

11:25.619 --> 11:28.186
WILL ALLOW US TO BEGIN
MARY'S TREATMENT ON SCHEDULE.

11:28.188 --> 11:29.821
<i> Arthur: OTTO,</i>
<i> MAY I ASK A QUESTION?</i>

11:29.823 --> 11:31.289
WHAT IS IT, ARTHUR?

11:31.291 --> 11:34.125
<i> IF THE SPECIMEN IN THE TANK</i>
<i> REGAINS CONSCIOUSNESS,</i>

11:34.127 --> 11:36.728
<i> WHAT SHOULD I REFER TO HIM AS?</i>

11:36.730 --> 11:37.829
<i> JIMMY PRITCHARD IS DEAD.</i>

11:37.831 --> 11:39.330
REFER TO HIM AS...

11:39.332 --> 11:41.166
PROPRIETARY
GOODWIN TECHNOLOGY.

11:41.168 --> 11:44.002
<i> SHOULD I RUN THAT NAME</i>
<i> BY MARY?</i>

11:44.004 --> 11:46.371
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

11:46.373 --> 11:48.239
[ GLASSES BEEPING ]

11:48.241 --> 11:52.243
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

11:52.245 --> 11:56.214
MARY? YOUR ONCOLOGIST
IS ON THE LINE.

11:57.718 --> 11:59.484
THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

11:59.486 --> 12:02.020
AS ALWAYS, I APPRECIATE
YOUR DISCRETION.

12:02.022 --> 12:06.991
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

12:06.993 --> 12:09.094
WHAT'S OUR CURRENT PRICE
PER SHARE?

12:09.096 --> 12:11.863
$476.98.

12:11.865 --> 12:13.364
STILL HOLDING EVEN -- GOOD.

12:13.366 --> 12:15.533
THE INTERVIEWS YOU'RE DOING
HAVE STABILIZED THE STOCK.

12:15.535 --> 12:16.534
LET'S LINE UP SOME MORE.

12:16.536 --> 12:17.702
SET A MEETING WITH P.R.

12:17.704 --> 12:18.837
RIGHT AWAY.

12:18.839 --> 12:20.538
TED TALKS HAVE ALWAYS
WANTED YOU, AS WELL.

12:20.540 --> 12:22.774
THEY'VE ALWAYS WANTED OTTO,
BUT THEY'LL TAKE ME,

12:22.776 --> 12:24.409
SO MAKE THAT HAPPEN,
AND, UH...

12:26.179 --> 12:27.579
[ SIGHS ]

12:27.581 --> 12:29.547
OKAY, ALEXA.

12:29.549 --> 12:31.049
WHAT'S WITH
THE MOTHER HEN LOOK?

12:31.051 --> 12:34.052
I'M SORRY.

12:34.054 --> 12:36.121
CAN I ASK WHAT
THE DOCTOR SAID?

12:36.123 --> 12:40.258
MY NUMBERS ARE GETTING WORSE.
CHEMO STILL ISN'T WORKING.

12:40.260 --> 12:42.761
THEN IS IT TIME TO LET THE BOARD
AND THE PUBLIC KNOW YOUR ILL

12:42.763 --> 12:44.929
AND THAT YOUR ILLNESS IS
WHAT'S DISTRACTING OTTO AND --

12:44.931 --> 12:46.197
GET AHEAD OF THE STORY?

12:46.199 --> 12:49.100
OF COURSE, YOU'VE ALREADY
CONSIDERED EVERYTHING.

12:49.102 --> 12:51.035
OTTO'S NOT READY FOR ANYONE
TO KNOW I'M SICK.

12:51.037 --> 12:52.804
I'M JUST YOUR ASSISTANT.

12:52.806 --> 12:54.606
AND THIS IS PROBABLY
NOT MY PLACE,

12:54.608 --> 12:56.574
BUT IF THE CHEMO
ISN'T WORKING,

12:56.576 --> 12:58.943
WON'T OTTO HAVE TO
START GETTING READY?

12:58.945 --> 13:02.213
THERE ARE NO OTHER TREATMENTS,
ARE THERE?

13:04.551 --> 13:06.551
<i> PHASE ONE COMPLETE.</i>

13:06.553 --> 13:08.787
<i> SHOULD I ATTEMPT TO RESTORE</i>
<i> CONSCIOUSNESS?</i>

13:08.789 --> 13:12.056
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

13:12.058 --> 13:14.559
MOM AND DAD BELIEVED
IN GOD, OTTO.

13:14.561 --> 13:16.427
THEY WOULD'VE SAID
WHAT WE'RE ABOUT TO DO

13:16.429 --> 13:17.462
SHOULD BE LEFT TO GOD.

13:17.464 --> 13:19.497
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

13:19.499 --> 13:21.299
THEY WOULD'VE SAID
WE'D BE PUNISHED

13:21.301 --> 13:22.600
FOR WHAT WE'RE ABOUT TO DO.

13:22.602 --> 13:25.670
THEY WOULD'VE WANTED US
TO TAKE CARE OF EACH OTHER.

13:25.672 --> 13:28.973
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

13:28.975 --> 13:33.144
FROM NOW ON,
NO MORE DECISIONS ON YOUR OWN.

13:33.146 --> 13:34.245
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

13:34.247 --> 13:37.582
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

13:37.584 --> 13:39.551
I PROMISE.

13:48.261 --> 13:49.928
INITIATE PHASE TWO,
ARTHUR.

13:49.930 --> 13:53.231
[ BEEPING,
ELECTRICITY CRACKLING ]

14:10.116 --> 14:11.549
[ GUNS COCK ]

14:13.053 --> 14:14.219
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICK ]

14:17.290 --> 14:19.991
[ BEEPING, CRACKLING CONTINUES ]

14:19.993 --> 14:22.360
[ GASPS ]

14:23.630 --> 14:25.830
<i> MARY, PLEASE RESTATE.</i>

14:25.832 --> 14:28.466
<i> I AM NOT PROGRAMMED</i>
<i> TO RECOGNIZE TWIN-SPEAK.</i>

14:31.338 --> 14:35.406
¶¶

14:39.179 --> 14:41.112
<i> PHASE TWO COMPLETE.</i>

14:48.822 --> 14:52.090
[ COUGHING ]

14:52.092 --> 14:53.992
[ SIGHS ]

14:53.994 --> 14:57.495
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

15:04.004 --> 15:07.672
YOUR CIGARETTES
HAVE BEEN REMOVED.

15:07.674 --> 15:10.708
[ SIGHS, GRUNTS ]

15:10.710 --> 15:12.844
[ SIGHS ]

15:12.846 --> 15:14.212
AND WHO WOULD YOU BE?

15:14.214 --> 15:17.348
MY NAME'S MARY --
MARY GOODWIN.

15:17.350 --> 15:19.717
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO BE AFRAID.

15:19.719 --> 15:21.052
DO I LOOK AFRAID?

15:21.054 --> 15:23.955
[ GRUNTS, COUGHS ]

15:23.957 --> 15:27.592
SO [COUGHS]

15:27.594 --> 15:29.794
DID WE, UH...

15:29.796 --> 15:32.463
DO I OWE YOU FOR
SOMETHING?

15:32.465 --> 15:35.199
NO. YOU DON'T OWE ME
ANYTHING.

15:35.201 --> 15:37.635
WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN
MY APARTMENT, MARY?

15:37.637 --> 15:39.470
YOU KNOW THIS IS
YOUR APARTMENT?

15:39.472 --> 15:41.406
GOOD.
THAT'S REALLY GOOD.

15:41.408 --> 15:43.975
YEAH, I KNOW THIS IS
MY APARTMENT.

15:43.977 --> 15:45.877
I WANT TO KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE DOING IN IT.

15:45.879 --> 15:48.446
AND WHY YOU TOOK MY SMOKES.

15:48.448 --> 15:49.981
BECAUSE THEY CAUSE CANCER.

15:49.983 --> 15:53.384
AND WHAT ABOUT YOUR NAME?
CAN YOU TELL ME YOUR NAME?

15:53.386 --> 15:56.220
WELL, LET'S SEE.
I'VE HAD IT FOR 75 YEARS.

15:56.222 --> 15:58.323
IT'S JIMMY PRITCHARD.

15:58.325 --> 16:01.259
WHAT ARE YOU -- SOME KIND OF...
VISITING NURSE?

16:01.261 --> 16:03.094
SOCIAL WORKER?
IS THAT IT?

16:03.096 --> 16:04.495
DID MY KIDS SEND YOU
TO CHECK ON ME?

16:04.497 --> 16:06.597
WELL, YOU CAN PUT IN YOUR REPORT
TO MY SPECIAL AGENT SON

16:06.599 --> 16:07.765
THAT I KNOW WHO I AM.

16:07.767 --> 16:09.934
I DON'T NEED ANYBODY
TO TAKE CARE OF ME.

16:09.936 --> 16:12.236
AND I FEEL FINE.

16:12.238 --> 16:15.506
I EVEN GOT
MY APPETITE BACK.

16:15.508 --> 16:18.343
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT BE HUNGRY.
I MADE A SANDWICH FOR YOU.

16:22.515 --> 16:24.916
[ Muffled ] MMM, GOD,
THAT'S GOOD.

16:24.918 --> 16:27.085
USUALLY, MY TEETH WOULD BOTHER
ME WITH SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

16:27.087 --> 16:29.487
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

16:32.826 --> 16:34.158
[ PLATE CLINKS ]

16:34.160 --> 16:37.628
MR. PRITCHARD, CAN YOU TELL ME
THE LAST THING YOU REMEMBER?

16:37.630 --> 16:42.767
WHY IS MY HAND LIKE THIS?

16:44.537 --> 16:46.604
WHO ARE YOU?

16:46.606 --> 16:48.539
<i> HIS RESPIRATION RATE</i>
<i> IS RISING.</i>

16:48.541 --> 16:50.842
<i> MARY GOODWIN.</i>
<i> I'M HERE TO HELP YOU.</i>

16:50.844 --> 16:52.510
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

16:52.512 --> 16:54.779
THEN WHY IS MY...

16:54.781 --> 16:58.416
HAND NOT MY HAND, MARY?

17:01.121 --> 17:04.989
MY VOICE SOUNDS FUNNY.
WAS THERE AN ACCIDENT?

17:04.991 --> 17:07.125
NO. NOT AN ACCIDENT.

17:07.127 --> 17:09.160
YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH SOMETHING,

17:09.162 --> 17:11.462
BUT IT'S GOING TO BE
OKAY, I PROMISE.

17:11.464 --> 17:12.997
WHAT DO YOU REMEMBER?

17:12.999 --> 17:18.302
[ Sighing ]
MY SON'S HOUSE AND...

17:18.304 --> 17:21.406
[ SIGHS ]
...A BRIDGE.

17:23.009 --> 17:24.842
THERE USED TO BE A MIRROR
RIGHT HERE.

17:24.844 --> 17:27.345
WHY DID YOU TAKE IT DOWN?

17:27.347 --> 17:29.347
BECAUSE WE NEED TO
DO THIS SLOWLY.

17:29.349 --> 17:32.383
DO...WHAT...SLOWLY?

17:36.656 --> 17:38.189
I KNOW YOU.

17:38.191 --> 17:40.191
<i> BLOOD PRESSURE</i>
<i> 170 OVER 120.</i>

17:40.193 --> 17:42.326
<i> I KNOW YOU.</i>
<i> YOU'RE ONE OF THOSE...</i>

17:42.328 --> 17:44.729
RICH COMPUTER TWITS.

17:44.731 --> 17:46.164
THE HELL ARE YOU DOING
IN MY APARTMENT?

17:46.166 --> 17:48.499
I THINK WE NEED TO
STOP NOW, OKAY?

17:48.501 --> 17:49.167
NO!

17:49.169 --> 17:50.368
[ BEEP ]

17:50.370 --> 17:51.669
<i> WE NEED TO STOP NOW, OKAY?</i>
MARY...

17:51.671 --> 17:52.904
<i> YOU'RE GONNA FEEL TIRED.</i>
...GET OUT OF THERE!

17:52.906 --> 17:54.005
<i> I NEED YOU TO SLEEP.</i>

17:54.007 --> 17:55.339
WHEN YOU WAKE UP,
WE CAN START AGAIN.

17:55.341 --> 17:56.374
OKAY, BUT RIGHT NOW --
AAH!

17:56.376 --> 17:57.275
I FELL!

17:57.277 --> 17:58.609
[ CRYING ]
I HIT THE GROUND! I...

17:58.611 --> 18:00.711
[ CRYING CONTINUES ]

18:00.713 --> 18:02.180
I HIT THE GROUND.

18:02.182 --> 18:04.849
[ GASPING ]

18:04.851 --> 18:07.085
I DIED.

18:07.087 --> 18:09.287
OH!

18:09.289 --> 18:11.456
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

18:11.458 --> 18:14.025
[ SIGHS ]

18:16.896 --> 18:18.796
WHY DIDN'T THE SEDATIVE
RELEASE?!

18:18.798 --> 18:20.131
<i> IT DID RELEASE.</i>

18:20.133 --> 18:23.201
<i> HIS BODY NEEDED 12 TIMES</i>
<i> THE PRESCRIBED AMOUNT.</i>

18:23.203 --> 18:25.903
HE'S STRONGER
THAN PREDICTED.

18:25.905 --> 18:29.273
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

18:29.275 --> 18:30.575
WE NEED TO KNOW HOW MUCH.

18:30.577 --> 18:32.743
KEEP HIM SEDATED UNTIL
WE RUN MORE TESTS.

18:32.745 --> 18:36.147
<i> I CAN'T. THE CAPSULE UNDER</i>
<i> HIS SKIN IS NOW EMPTY.</i>

18:42.989 --> 18:45.656
[ SIGHS ]

18:54.801 --> 18:57.068
[ SIGHS ]

19:00.473 --> 19:03.474
[ METAL CLATTERS ]

19:03.476 --> 19:06.277
[ GRUNTS ]

19:06.279 --> 19:09.514
[ GRUNTS ]

19:21.427 --> 19:22.260
Jimmy: OPEN IT!

19:22.262 --> 19:23.628
[ POUNDING ON DOOR ]

19:23.630 --> 19:28.432
LET ME OUT!

19:28.434 --> 19:29.100
[ GRUNTS ]

19:29.102 --> 19:30.535
[ CLATTERING ]

19:30.537 --> 19:31.936
[ ALARM BLARING ]

19:31.938 --> 19:33.838
<i> HE'S BROKEN THROUGH</i>
<i> THE BACK WALL OF THE ROOM.</i>

19:33.840 --> 19:36.140
<i> HE'S IN THE HOUSE.</i>

19:36.142 --> 19:40.845
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

19:52.725 --> 19:56.527
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

20:01.668 --> 20:05.403
[ SIGHS ]

20:10.743 --> 20:14.145
[ BEEP ]

20:14.147 --> 20:16.247
Mary: WE'RE OFFERING YOU
ANOTHER CHANCE.

20:17.984 --> 20:21.319
WHAT? WHY DID YOU
DO THIS TO ME?

20:21.321 --> 20:24.021
YOU HAVE A VERY RARE
GENETIC PRECURSOR

20:24.023 --> 20:26.257
WHICH ALLOWED US TO RECODE
AND REGENERATE YOUR CELLS.

20:26.259 --> 20:27.892
I DON'T KNOW WHAT ANY
OF THAT MEANS, BUT THIS...

20:27.894 --> 20:31.662
THIS IS<i> ME.</i>
BUT THIS ISN'T<i> ME!</i>

20:31.664 --> 20:34.999
THIS IS THE BEST VERSION
OF YOU.

20:35.001 --> 20:37.835
YOU'RE THE FIRST TO JOURNEY
ALL THE WAY BACK.

20:37.837 --> 20:40.204
TO GET ANOTHER CHANCE.

20:40.206 --> 20:41.672
[ SIGHS ]

20:41.674 --> 20:43.341
DON'T YOU WANT IT?

20:43.343 --> 20:47.378
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

20:47.380 --> 20:48.679
WITH ANOTHER CHANCE,

20:48.681 --> 20:51.382
MAYBE YOU DON'T HAVE TO
END IT THAT WAY.

20:51.384 --> 20:54.085
[ SIGHS ] IS...

20:54.087 --> 20:56.954
IS THAT WHAT PEOPLE THINK?

20:56.956 --> 20:59.423
THEY THINK I JUMPED...

20:59.425 --> 21:01.259
OFF THAT BRIDGE?

21:01.261 --> 21:02.593
YOUR MEMORY'S BEEN THROUGH
A SHOCK.

21:02.595 --> 21:04.228
YOU MIGHT NOT BE READY
TO REMEMBER WHAT YOU DID.

21:04.230 --> 21:08.199
NO! THERE WAS A BREAK-IN
IN MY SON'S HOUSE.

21:08.201 --> 21:10.768
I CAUGHT THEM, AND THEN
THEY THREW ME OFF THAT BRIDGE.

21:12.138 --> 21:15.139
NO, WAIT.

21:15.141 --> 21:17.808
IT WAS NOT A -- NOT A...
NOT A BREAK-IN.

21:17.810 --> 21:20.144
THEY WERE...

21:20.146 --> 21:22.413
THEY WERE LOOKING
FOR SOMETHING, BUT...

21:22.415 --> 21:28.119
I WAS JUST AN OLD MAN,
SO THEY JUST...

21:28.121 --> 21:31.155
TOSSED ME LIKE
A BAG OF DIRT.

21:36.095 --> 21:38.195
I WAS JUST AN OLD MAN,
WASN'T I?

21:44.404 --> 21:47.305
I DON'T CARE IF YOU BELIEVE ME.
MY SON IS IN TROUBLE.

21:47.307 --> 21:50.474
[ GRUNTS ]

21:50.476 --> 21:53.311
[ GASPS ]

21:53.313 --> 21:57.415
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

21:57.417 --> 22:01.018
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

22:01.020 --> 22:04.622
[ HEART BEATING LOUDLY ]

22:04.624 --> 22:08.459
[ BIRD CRIES ]

22:08.461 --> 22:13.698
[ INSECTS BUZZING ]

22:17.103 --> 22:20.004
[ WINGS WHIRRING ]

22:20.006 --> 22:22.106
[ LEASH RATTLING ]

22:22.108 --> 22:25.543
[ DOG GROWLING, BARKS ]

22:25.545 --> 22:27.778
¶¶

22:31.150 --> 22:34.685
[ DOG BARKING ]

22:34.687 --> 22:37.021
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

22:37.023 --> 22:38.889
[ DOG GROWLING ]

22:40.326 --> 22:42.426
[ DOG PANTING ]

22:43.896 --> 22:45.529
NICE DAY FOR A HIKE.

22:45.531 --> 22:47.865
YEAH, IT IS.

22:47.867 --> 22:50.368
TRAINER, RIGHT?
GYM OR PRIVATE?

22:50.370 --> 22:52.737
PRIVATE?

22:52.739 --> 22:57.208
WHAT DO YOU DO -- TRX,
P90X, KETTLEBELLS, SLT?

22:57.210 --> 22:59.176
BECAUSE...
YOU FEEL THIS?

22:59.178 --> 23:00.511
[ SIGHS ]

23:00.513 --> 23:04.148
NO MATTER WHAT I DO, THERE'S
LIKE 2% THAT I CAN'T GET RID OF.

23:04.150 --> 23:04.982
FEEL THAT.

23:04.984 --> 23:06.317
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

23:06.319 --> 23:08.319
YEP, I FEEL IT.

23:08.321 --> 23:09.353
ARE YOU TAKING
NEW CLIENTS?

23:09.355 --> 23:10.087
[ SIGHS ]

23:10.089 --> 23:13.057
UM...NO, NOT RIGHT NOW.

23:13.059 --> 23:14.158
OKAY.

23:14.160 --> 23:16.160
SEE YOU THEN.

23:20.733 --> 23:23.501
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:23.503 --> 23:26.604
¶¶

23:30.576 --> 23:33.511
Mary: HE WAS IN THE SHERIFF'S
DEPARTMENT FOR 30 YEARS.

23:33.513 --> 23:36.180
HE'LL TRY TO FIND OUT WHO
BROKE INTO HIS SON'S HOUSE.

23:36.182 --> 23:39.216
HE'LL TRY TO SOLVE THE CRIME.

23:39.218 --> 23:42.219
<i> MARY, I DON'T MEAN</i>
<i> TO DISAGREE WITH YOU</i>

23:42.221 --> 23:44.688
<i> ABOUT MR. PRITCHARD'S</i>
<i> CURRENT INTENTIONS,</i>

23:44.690 --> 23:47.892
<i> BUT MY LIST OF HIS PRIORITIES</i>
<i> RANKS LAW ENFORCEMENT</i>

23:47.894 --> 23:50.461
<i> BELOW WOMEN, ALCOHOL,</i>
<i> AND MUSIC.</i>

23:50.463 --> 23:52.596
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

23:52.598 --> 23:54.765
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

24:11.951 --> 24:13.818
HI!

24:13.820 --> 24:16.654
HI.

24:16.656 --> 24:18.222
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:18.224 --> 24:19.824
WHAT?

24:19.826 --> 24:21.158
IT'S LOUD IN HERE!

24:21.160 --> 24:23.627
DO I KNOW YOU?

24:23.629 --> 24:26.263
NO, BUT...

24:26.265 --> 24:29.266
I KNOW A FRIEND OF YOURS.
JIMMY PRITCHARD.

24:29.268 --> 24:32.002
HE SAID YOU
HANG OUT HERE.

24:32.004 --> 24:33.737
SHERIFF PRITCHARD
KILLED HIMSELF.

24:33.739 --> 24:37.141
YEAH. YEAH,
I READ ABOUT THAT,

24:37.143 --> 24:40.344
BUT HE SAID THAT IF I EVER NEED
ANYTHING, THAT I SHOULD SEE YOU.

24:40.346 --> 24:42.246
AND WHAT DO YOU WANT?

24:42.248 --> 24:44.181
I WANT TO GO TO YOUR PLACE.

24:44.183 --> 24:47.485
YOU SAY YOU'RE A FRIEND
OF JIMMY'S?

24:47.487 --> 24:48.486
UH-HUH.

24:48.488 --> 24:50.287
I DIDN'T SEE YOU
AT HIS FUNERAL.

24:50.289 --> 24:53.491
YOU WERE AT M--

24:53.493 --> 24:54.658
YOU WERE AT THE FUNERAL?

24:54.660 --> 24:55.960
YEAH.

24:55.962 --> 24:58.162
HOW WAS IT?
UH...

24:58.164 --> 25:00.965
REAL SAD...I GUESS?

25:00.967 --> 25:02.867
NO.

25:02.869 --> 25:04.668
THERE WAS HARDLY
ANY WEEPING.

25:08.107 --> 25:11.141
BIG TURNOUT?

25:11.143 --> 25:13.611
WOULD YOU LIKE TO
BUY ME A DRINK?

25:13.613 --> 25:15.513
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:15.515 --> 25:19.450
THE THING IS, I'M KIND OF
TAPPED OUT RIGHT NOW.

25:19.452 --> 25:22.119
AND SO CONCLUDES
OUR TIME TOGETHER.

25:22.121 --> 25:25.456
BUT -- BUT I'M A FRIEND
OF JIMMY'S.

25:25.458 --> 25:28.058
THEN YOU SHOULD UNDERSTAND
THE NATURE OF OUR RELATIONSHIP.

25:28.060 --> 25:29.727
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC CONTINUES ]

25:38.170 --> 25:40.237
DON'T MOVE.

25:47.980 --> 25:50.247
ROOM'S SINGLE USE, BRO.

25:50.249 --> 25:52.983
YOU LOOK FIT.
YOU DO KETTLEBELLS?

25:52.985 --> 25:55.052
DO I DO KETTLE--
ANSWER.

25:55.054 --> 25:56.820
[ GRUNTS ]

25:57.990 --> 25:58.989
FOUND YOUR SECRET.

25:58.991 --> 26:00.224
YOU A COP?

26:00.226 --> 26:02.226
I'M JUST GONNA NEED
YOUR BANKROLL NOW, BUDDY.

26:02.228 --> 26:03.894
[ GROANS ]

26:06.666 --> 26:08.999
HUH, I'LL HAVE TO GET
A HANDLE ON THAT.

26:09.001 --> 26:13.003
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC CONTINUES ]

26:13.005 --> 26:16.040
[ CHUCKLES ]
THIS WILL DO.

26:16.042 --> 26:18.175
WHAT KIND OF COP
ARE YOU?!

26:18.177 --> 26:20.277
SONNY, I'M THE SHERIFF.

26:20.279 --> 26:21.845
¶ DON'T DO IT, DON'T DO IT ¶

26:21.847 --> 26:23.747
¶ DON'T TOUCH THE BASS ¶

26:23.749 --> 26:25.549
¶ DON'T DO IT, DON'T DO IT ¶

26:25.551 --> 26:27.351
¶ DON'T TOUCH MY ¶

26:27.353 --> 26:30.020
YOU JUST WANT TO USE
MY COMPUTER?

26:30.022 --> 26:31.789
IT HAS THE INTERNET,
RIGHT?

26:31.791 --> 26:37.027
YES. IT HAS...
THE INTERNET.

26:37.029 --> 26:38.796
THAT'S ALL YOU
WANT TO DO?

26:38.798 --> 26:40.297
MY COMPUTER?

26:40.299 --> 26:41.298
MM-HMM.

26:41.300 --> 26:42.967
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

26:42.969 --> 26:44.969
WELL, I'M GONNA GO
TAKE A SHOWER.

26:44.971 --> 26:46.704
YOU CAN GET
YOUR CYBER-FREAK ON.

26:49.976 --> 26:52.977
[ BEEPING ]

26:52.979 --> 26:54.812
<i> Mary: WHAT ARE YOU DOING,</i>
<i> MR. PRITCHARD?</i>

26:54.814 --> 26:57.481
<i> HERE, MR. PRITCHARD,</i>
<i> ON THE SCREEN.</i>

26:57.483 --> 26:59.817
<i> YOUR FRIEND BETTINA'S</i>
<i> ON LOOKING GLASS.</i>

26:59.819 --> 27:02.086
<i> WE'VE BEEN LISTENING FOR</i>
<i> YOUR VOICE PATTERN.</i>

27:02.088 --> 27:03.220
ON HER COMPUTER?

27:03.222 --> 27:05.456
<i> ON TWO BILLION COMPUTERS</i>
<i> AND DEVICES.</i>

27:06.626 --> 27:08.926
IS IT YOUR PLAN TO HAVE SEX
WITH THAT WOMAN?

27:08.928 --> 27:11.295
IS IT MY PLAN
TO HAVE WHAT?

27:11.297 --> 27:13.998
<i> IF YOU DO, YOU'RE MOST LIKELY</i>
<i> SUPER-POTENT.</i>

27:14.000 --> 27:15.299
<i> DO YOU HAVE PROTECTION?</i>

27:15.301 --> 27:17.501
SUPER-- LADY, I'M JUST
TRYING TO FIND OUT

27:17.503 --> 27:19.303
ABOUT THE BREAK-IN
AT MY SON'S HOUSE.

27:19.305 --> 27:20.971
<i> THERE'S NO RECORD</i>
<i> OF A BREAK-IN.</i>

27:20.973 --> 27:22.606
<i> I'VE SEARCHED EVERY DATABASE</i>
<i> FOR ONE.</i>

27:22.608 --> 27:24.608
WELL, THEN HE DOESN'T KNOW
THEY WERE THERE.

27:24.610 --> 27:25.943
I MEAN, HOW COULD
HE NOT NOTICE

27:25.945 --> 27:27.511
THAT SOMEBODY'S GONE
THROUGH HIS THINGS?

27:27.513 --> 27:28.779
I MEAN,
WHERE'S HIS HEAD AT?

27:28.781 --> 27:31.115
I HAVE TO SIT HIM DOWN
ABOUT THAT.

27:31.117 --> 27:34.151
<i> MR. PRITCHARD, YOU CAN'T</i>
<i> SIT HIM DOWN ABOUT ANYTHING.</i>

27:34.153 --> 27:37.421
<i> YOUR FAMILY BURIED YOU.</i>

27:37.423 --> 27:39.990
<i> LOOK.</i>

27:42.261 --> 27:43.961
MAKE IT BIGGER.

27:43.963 --> 27:46.096
[ BEEPING ]

27:49.702 --> 27:52.670
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
SON OF A BITCH.

27:52.672 --> 27:55.272
MY KILLER WAS CARRYING
MY OWN DAMN CASKET.

27:56.375 --> 27:58.876
<i> "JOHN STRAYBURN."</i>

27:58.878 --> 28:01.478
I KNOW THAT NAME.
THAT'S MY SON'S PARTNER.

28:01.480 --> 28:03.147
YOU DONE?

28:03.149 --> 28:04.682
<i> WE NEED YOU TO GET BACK HERE</i>
<i> RIGHT --</i>

28:06.552 --> 28:09.053
BABY, IT IS MESSED UP
IF YOU WOULD RATHER DO IT

28:09.055 --> 28:12.156
ONLINE LIKE THAT...THAN WHEN YOU
HAVE SOMEONE HERE IN THE FLESH.

28:12.158 --> 28:13.724
¶ BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM ¶

28:13.726 --> 28:15.492
¶ BOOM, BOOM, BOOM ¶

28:15.494 --> 28:17.327
¶ BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM ¶

28:17.329 --> 28:19.329
THIS DOES NOTHING FOR YOU?
¶ BOOM, BOOM, BOOM ¶

28:19.331 --> 28:21.331
¶ BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM ¶

28:21.333 --> 28:22.966
¶ BOOM, BOOM, BOOM ¶
YOU KNOW...

28:22.968 --> 28:24.168
¶ BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM ¶

28:24.170 --> 28:25.369
PRITCHARD TOLD ME THAT

28:25.371 --> 28:29.540
HE, UH, WAS TOO OLD TO REALLY
DO MUCH OF ANYTHING.

28:29.542 --> 28:31.842
I DON'T REALLY LIKE TO
TALK ABOUT MY OTHER CLIENTS.

28:31.844 --> 28:32.643
MM-HMM.

28:32.645 --> 28:34.011
¶ BOOM, BOOM, BOOM ¶

28:34.013 --> 28:35.846
¶ BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM ¶

28:35.848 --> 28:37.681
¶ BOOM, BOOM, BOOM ¶

28:37.683 --> 28:39.550
¶ BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM ¶

28:39.552 --> 28:41.318
¶ BOOM, BOOM, BOOM ¶

28:41.320 --> 28:43.520
¶ BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM ¶
MM, UH...

28:43.522 --> 28:44.488
¶ BOOM, BOOM, BOOM ¶

28:44.490 --> 28:45.823
DO YOU HAVE PROTECTION?
'CAUSE...

28:45.825 --> 28:47.191
¶ BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM, BA-BOOM ¶

28:47.193 --> 28:49.193
...THERE'S A CHANCE
I MIGHT BE SUPER-POTENT.

28:49.195 --> 28:50.260
[ LAUGHS ]

28:50.262 --> 28:53.263
¶ DON'T TOUCH MY ¶

28:53.265 --> 28:54.665
Man:
THERE YOU GO! GOOD!

28:54.667 --> 28:56.266
COACH...
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

28:56.268 --> 28:58.936
THAT'S IT! THAT'S IT!
THERE YOU GO!

28:58.938 --> 29:00.170
A LOT OF HUSTLE THERE!

29:00.172 --> 29:01.905
YOU GIRLS WILL BE IN
IN A MINUTE, ALL RIGHT?

29:03.075 --> 29:05.075
DAMN IT, HE'S THE COACH.

29:06.679 --> 29:07.911
GOOD!
BRING IT AROUND!

29:07.913 --> 29:11.515
THAT'S IT!
THERE YOU GO!

29:11.517 --> 29:15.018
GIVE HER A TARGET
ON THE WING!

29:15.020 --> 29:16.954
I ASK THAT PARENTS
STAY OVER THERE.

29:16.956 --> 29:19.289
JACKIE,
WATCH THAT LEFT FOOT!

29:19.291 --> 29:20.758
Woman: OH, YEAH!

29:20.760 --> 29:23.727
UH...
I'M NOT A PARENT.

29:23.729 --> 29:25.562
I KNEW YOUR FATHER.

29:25.564 --> 29:28.899
AND, UH, THERE'S SOMETHING
WE NEED TO TALK ABOUT.

29:28.901 --> 29:30.100
NICE JOB, SARAH!

29:30.102 --> 29:31.301
CUT DOWN THAT ANGLE!

29:31.303 --> 29:33.103
Man: BLOCK, GINA!

29:33.105 --> 29:34.738
LET ME GUESS.
HE OWED YOU MONEY?

29:34.740 --> 29:37.608
NO. NOTHING LIKE THAT.

29:37.610 --> 29:39.977
I'M COACHING MY GIRL'S
SOCCER GAME, ALL RIGHT?

29:39.979 --> 29:43.113
WAIT OVER THERE, AND I'LL GIVE
YOU FIVE MINUTES WHEN IT'S OVER.

29:43.115 --> 29:44.314
THIS IS IMPORTANT.

29:44.316 --> 29:46.049
SO IS THIS.
WE'LL TALK LATER.

29:46.051 --> 29:47.084
Gracie: DAD?
YEAH?

29:47.086 --> 29:47.918
CAN ROBIN AND I SWITCH?

29:47.920 --> 29:48.919
SHE WANTS TO PLAY RIGHT-MID?

29:48.921 --> 29:50.154
UH...
SAY IT'S OKAY.

29:50.156 --> 29:52.623
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

29:52.625 --> 29:54.758
SORRY.
MISTER, DO I KNOW YOU?

29:54.760 --> 29:58.395
NO.
YOU DON'T KNOW ME.

29:58.397 --> 30:01.298
THERE YOU GO!
WATCH THAT LEFT FOOT!

30:01.300 --> 30:02.166
GOOD!

30:02.168 --> 30:05.402
TELL ROBIN RIGHT-MID,
OKAY?

30:05.404 --> 30:08.672
WHY ARE YOU STILL
STANDING HERE?

30:08.674 --> 30:10.174
I'LL WAIT OVER THERE.

30:10.176 --> 30:11.909
[ SIGHS ]

30:11.911 --> 30:14.144
THAT'S IT, THAT'S IT!
THAT WAS GOOD!

30:14.146 --> 30:15.479
LOTS OF HUSTLE!

30:15.481 --> 30:17.314
Woman: YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
CUT THAT OFF!

30:17.316 --> 30:19.149
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

30:19.151 --> 30:21.385
[ SHOUTING ECHOES, WARBLING ]

30:23.823 --> 30:25.455
Man:
TEAM LOOKS GOOD, GIRLS!

30:25.457 --> 30:26.824
MAKE SURE YOU'RE READY.

30:26.826 --> 30:29.793
SAW YOU TALKING TO SUPER DAD.
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:29.795 --> 30:30.994
HE'S MY BIG BROTHER.

30:30.996 --> 30:32.162
HELEN?

30:32.164 --> 30:35.332
YEAH.

30:35.334 --> 30:36.700
[ SHOUTING ECHOES ]

30:36.702 --> 30:37.835
[ Echoing ] ARE YOU OKAY?

30:37.837 --> 30:40.170
NO.

30:40.172 --> 30:42.940
SOMETHING'S WRONG. IT'S...

30:52.484 --> 30:54.117
THE PROCESS IS LIKE
A TRANSPLANT.

30:54.119 --> 30:55.319
YOUR BODY'S GOING
INTO REJECTION.

30:55.321 --> 30:56.687
MY SON IS IN TROUBLE.

30:56.689 --> 30:58.488
YOU CAN'T HELP HIM
LIKE THIS.

30:58.490 --> 31:01.258
COME WITH ME NOW
BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE.

31:03.729 --> 31:06.864
¶¶

31:12.838 --> 31:17.841
I KNOW YOU CAN SEE ME,
SO LOOK.

31:17.843 --> 31:20.310
I'M GOING TO HELP YOU
HELP YOUR SON.

31:24.149 --> 31:27.217
DEPOSITS INTO STRAYBURN'S
ACCOUNT AFTER EACH ROBBERY.

31:27.219 --> 31:30.387
TEXTS TO STRAYBURN
BEFORE EACH ROBBERY.

31:30.389 --> 31:33.490
SHOW THIS TO DUVAL.

31:33.492 --> 31:36.159
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

31:36.161 --> 31:38.829
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

31:45.571 --> 31:48.639
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

32:02.288 --> 32:05.455
WHY'D YOU REALLY
DO THIS TO ME, MARY?

32:08.394 --> 32:10.761
[ SIGHS ]

32:10.763 --> 32:14.131
I HAVE CANCER.
THERE'S NO CURE.

32:14.133 --> 32:16.366
CHEMO STOPPED WORKING
SIX MONTHS AGO.

32:16.368 --> 32:17.701
[ MONITOR BEEPS ]

32:17.703 --> 32:21.071
OTTO RECODED YOUR RED BLOOD
CELLS TO FIGHT OFF DEATH.

32:21.073 --> 32:26.410
NOW HE'S USING THEM TO FIGHT
THE CANCER IN MY BLOOD.

32:26.412 --> 32:29.746
THIS IS YOU GOING IN ME.

32:29.748 --> 32:31.815
[ SIGHS ]

32:31.817 --> 32:33.650
YOU BROUGHT ME BACK...

32:33.652 --> 32:37.087
TO SAVE YOU?

32:37.089 --> 32:38.655
AND...

32:38.657 --> 32:40.757
THAT IN THERE, THAT'S...

32:40.759 --> 32:42.326
THAT'S ME?

32:42.328 --> 32:44.328
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

32:44.330 --> 32:46.763
[ SIGHS ]

32:46.765 --> 32:48.832
LOOK, I'M 75 YEARS OLD.

32:48.834 --> 32:50.901
I'VE SEEN A LOT OF MY FRIENDS GO
TO CANCER, AND IT AIN'T PRETTY.

32:50.903 --> 32:51.835
I FEEL FOR YOU.

32:51.837 --> 32:54.304
BUT OTHER PEOPLE
DON'T DO THIS.

32:54.306 --> 32:56.506
OTTO IS NOT OTHER PEOPLE.

32:56.508 --> 33:00.143
<i> OTTO?</i>
<i> YOU'RE THE ONE DYING.</i>

33:00.145 --> 33:03.080
<i> OTTO CAN'T BE</i>
<i> WITHOUT ME.</i>

33:03.082 --> 33:06.149
<i> MAYBE OTTO COULD FIND HIMSELF</i>
<i> A WOMAN WHO ISN'T HIS SISTER?</i>

33:06.151 --> 33:08.018
MY ROOM, 1988!

33:08.020 --> 33:09.152
<i> Arthur:</i>
<i>YOU KNOW YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO</i>

33:09.154 --> 33:10.854
<i> MANAGE YOUR FEELINGS THIS WAY.</i>

33:10.856 --> 33:13.123
<i> MARY PREFERS YOU STAY PRESENT.</i>

33:13.125 --> 33:16.026
<i> I SPOKE FOR HIM</i>
<i> UNTIL HE WAS 9.</i>

33:16.028 --> 33:18.996
HE EXPERIENCES
THE WORLD THROUGH ME.

33:18.998 --> 33:22.299
IF I GO, HE'LL RETREAT
INTO HIMSELF.

33:22.301 --> 33:25.335
HE'LL BE LOST.

33:25.337 --> 33:28.105
SO GO SAVE YOUR SON.

33:28.107 --> 33:30.874
BUT THEN COME BACK TO US.

33:33.312 --> 33:35.679
YOU'LL BE NEEDING A CAR.

33:35.681 --> 33:39.082
¶¶

33:41.053 --> 33:43.820
IT WAS OUR FATHER'S.

33:43.822 --> 33:46.990
SUITS YOU.

33:46.992 --> 33:49.026
YOU HAVE 12 HOURS BEFORE YOU
NEED TO BE BACK IN THE TANK.

33:49.028 --> 33:52.729
SET THE TIMER ON
THE PHONE FOR YOU.

33:56.168 --> 33:58.668
MAYBE YOU DIG THIS
COPS-AND-ROBBERS STUFF.

33:58.670 --> 34:03.907
¶ BUT THEY SAID IT
AT THE BIG AND TALL ¶

34:03.909 --> 34:06.343
¶ A FADED KING, LIKE A PRINCE ¶

34:06.345 --> 34:11.581
¶ AND A JOKER'S PAIR
OF COVERALLS ¶

34:11.583 --> 34:13.083
¶ WHEN THE MOTOR CHASE STARTS ¶

34:13.085 --> 34:14.851
OH, YEAH.

34:14.853 --> 34:16.553
THIS WILL DO.

34:18.157 --> 34:22.025
¶ THERE'S NO GETTING OUT
OF THIS ONE ¶

34:22.027 --> 34:26.530
YOU'VE GOT 10 SECONDS TO EXPLAIN
WHY YOU'RE OUTSIDE MY HOUSE.

34:26.532 --> 34:29.533
READ THIS.
THEN WE'LL TALK.

34:29.535 --> 34:31.935
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

34:36.575 --> 34:38.708
IT'S A NICE HOUSE.

34:38.710 --> 34:41.378
LOOKS LIKE A REAL NICE PLACE
TO RAISE A FAMILY.

34:41.380 --> 34:43.280
UNTIL I FIGURE OUT
WHAT YOU WANT,

34:43.282 --> 34:45.482
IT'S BEST YOU DON'T
MENTION MY FAMILY.

34:51.790 --> 34:54.091
THIS IS CRAP.
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

34:54.093 --> 34:55.625
YOU GO CHECK IT OUT THEN.

34:55.627 --> 34:57.027
AND YOU CAME BY THIS HOW?

34:57.029 --> 34:57.961
[ SIGHS ]

34:57.963 --> 34:59.896
YOUR FATHER DIDN'T TRUST
STRAYBURN.

34:59.898 --> 35:00.931
MY FATHER?

35:00.933 --> 35:02.599
I DIDN'T THINK HE KNEW
MY PARTNER.

35:02.601 --> 35:04.768
[ CHIRPING CONTINUES ]

35:04.770 --> 35:07.637
I LOOKED THROUGH THESE RECORDS.
I DIDN'T SEE ANY OF THIS.

35:07.639 --> 35:08.972
JUST USE THE FILE, DUVAL.

35:08.974 --> 35:12.109
CLOSE THE CASE.
IT'LL MAKE YOUR CAREER.

35:13.612 --> 35:15.779
AND HOW EXACTLY DID YOU
KNOW MY FATHER?

35:15.781 --> 35:20.083
I DID SOME WORK FOR HIM.
USED TO TALK ABOUT YOU.

35:20.085 --> 35:22.752
SAID HOW PROUD HE WAS
OF YOU RAISING THAT LITTLE GIRL,

35:22.754 --> 35:25.122
GRACIE, ON YOUR OWN.

35:25.124 --> 35:27.290
HE WASN'T ALWAYS AMAZED
AT HOW WELL YOU TURNED OUT

35:27.292 --> 35:31.328
SEEING WHAT A TERRIBLE FATHER
HE WAS.

35:33.799 --> 35:35.465
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
DISPUTE THAT, HUH?

35:35.467 --> 35:37.134
WHY DON'T YOU
COME IN WITH ME?

35:39.271 --> 35:41.238
JUST PUT THIS UNDER
ANONYMOUS TIP.

35:41.240 --> 35:43.473
JUST KEEP MY NAME
THAT WAY, TOO.

35:43.475 --> 35:45.609
IT'S FUNNY.

35:45.611 --> 35:49.146
MY PARTNER WAS MORE FAMILY
TO ME THAN MY DAD EVER WAS.

35:49.148 --> 35:51.648
[ SIGHS ] YOU KNOW,
HE DID WHAT HE HAD TO DO

35:51.650 --> 35:53.116
TO KEEP THIS COUNTY
AND HIS FAMILY SAFE.

35:53.118 --> 35:53.917
"WHAT HE HAD TO DO"?

35:53.919 --> 35:54.818
YEAH.
[ SCOFFS ]

35:54.820 --> 35:56.019
YOU MEAN LIKE
PLANTING EVIDENCE

35:56.021 --> 35:58.188
INSTEAD OF COMING HOME
AT NIGHT?

35:58.190 --> 36:01.024
NO. HE DID WHAT
HE<i> WANTED</i> TO DO.

36:02.094 --> 36:04.161
HE WAS SELFISH TO THE END.

36:04.163 --> 36:06.763
LIKE WALKING OFF
THAT BRIDGE.

36:09.701 --> 36:11.868
YOU SOUND RELIEVED
HE'S GONE.

36:17.476 --> 36:19.476
OKAY, KID.

36:19.478 --> 36:22.112
I'LL STAY GONE.
[ SIGHS ]

36:22.114 --> 36:24.614
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

36:24.616 --> 36:26.816
<i> Arthur: MR. PRITCHARD</i>
<i> HAS LEFT HIS SON.</i>

36:26.818 --> 36:29.486
<i> HE SEEMS TO BE ENTERING</i>
<i> A BAR.</i>

36:29.488 --> 36:34.824
[ CREEDENCE CLEARWATER REVIVAL'S
"BAD MOON RISING" PLAYS ]

36:34.826 --> 36:39.996
Jimmy: ¶ I SEE
THE BAD MOON RISING ¶

36:39.998 --> 36:44.968
¶ I SEE TROUBLE ON THE WAY ¶

36:44.970 --> 36:46.903
¶ I SEE EARTHQUAKES
AND LIGHTNIN' ¶

36:46.905 --> 36:48.238
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

36:48.240 --> 36:50.140
[ MONITOR BEEPS ]

37:09.661 --> 37:10.660
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

37:10.662 --> 37:12.495
I DIDN'T WANT TO BELIEVE IT,

37:12.497 --> 37:16.166
BUT [SIGHS] IT ALL
CHECKS OUT, CHIEF.

37:16.168 --> 37:18.001
HE'S DIRTY.

37:24.009 --> 37:25.909
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

37:33.252 --> 37:38.622
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

37:38.624 --> 37:41.625
WHAT IF IT'S NOT JUST
MY SON'S PARTNER?

37:41.627 --> 37:43.126
WHAT IF IT GOES DEEPER?

37:43.128 --> 37:44.461
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

37:44.463 --> 37:45.762
Helen: HEY.

37:45.764 --> 37:48.865
HEY. REMEMBER THAT GUY AT
THE SOCCER GAME THE OTHER DAY?

37:48.867 --> 37:51.701
SURE, I REMEMBER HIM.
WHY? WHAT ABOUT HIM?

37:51.703 --> 37:53.637
I SAW HIM TODAY.

37:53.639 --> 37:55.138
YOU AND ME MADE A DEAL
WITH THESE GUYS,

37:55.140 --> 37:57.807
SO THIS NEEDS TO GO AWAY --
RIGHT NOW.

37:57.809 --> 38:00.110
[ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS ]

38:02.881 --> 38:06.383
IT'S LIKE I KNEW HIM,
BUT I'D NEVER MET HIM.

38:06.385 --> 38:09.119
He was close with Dad.

38:09.121 --> 38:12.689
YOU KNOW, DAD WASN'T ALWAYS
EXACTLY FAITHFUL TO MOM.

38:14.159 --> 38:17.827
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING -- WE HAVE
A BROTHER WE DIDN'T KNOW ABOUT?

38:21.333 --> 38:23.300
Hello?

38:23.302 --> 38:25.835
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

38:25.837 --> 38:28.638
[ Beep ]
<i> You've reached the voicemail</i>
<i> for Duval Pritchard.</i>

38:28.640 --> 38:29.806
<i> Please leave a message.</i>

38:34.079 --> 38:36.980
THOUGHT I WAS DONE
WITH HIM, BUT [SIGHS]

38:36.982 --> 38:38.748
YOU'RE NEVER DONE
WITH YOUR KIDS.

38:38.750 --> 38:41.985
PLEASE, JUST...
HELP ME FIND HIM.

38:41.987 --> 38:45.088
<i> YOU HAVE LESS THAN AN HOUR.</i>
<i> LOOK AT YOUR TIMER.</i>

38:45.090 --> 38:46.589
<i> YOU NEED TO COME BACK NOW.</i>

38:46.591 --> 38:49.459
FULL REJECTION LEAVES US
WITH NOTHING TO WORK WITH.

38:49.461 --> 38:51.061
DEATH THIS TIME IS FOR GOOD.

38:52.464 --> 38:53.697
<i> [ SIGHS ]</i>

38:53.699 --> 38:55.231
<i> ARE YOU SHOWING ANY SIGNS</i>
<i> OF REJECTION?</i>

38:56.935 --> 38:59.002
NO.

39:00.439 --> 39:01.971
WHERE'D YOU GET
THE FILE, DUVAL?

39:01.973 --> 39:04.140
HOW COULD YOU GET INTO
BUSINESS WITH THESE GUYS?

39:04.142 --> 39:05.108
YOU'RE MY PARTNER.

39:05.110 --> 39:06.309
AND YOU KNOW HOW IT IS.

39:06.311 --> 39:08.311
YOU TAKE A LITTLE,
AND THEN YOU TAKE A LITTLE MORE,

39:08.313 --> 39:09.312
AND THEN YOU CAN'T GET OUT.

39:09.314 --> 39:10.447
YOU SHOULD'VE COME TO ME!

39:10.449 --> 39:12.315
WHERE DID YOU GET
THAT FILE?!

39:12.317 --> 39:13.983
GO TO HELL.

39:13.985 --> 39:16.853
FUNNY.
THAT'S WHAT YOUR DAD SAID.

39:18.223 --> 39:22.826
ALL RIGHT, WE'RE HERE.
BRING HIM OUT.

39:22.828 --> 39:25.295
<i> YOUR SON'S PHONE SHOULD BE</i>
<i> 50 YARDS STRAIGHT AHEAD.</i>

39:25.297 --> 39:25.995
DO YOU SEE HIM?

39:25.997 --> 39:27.630
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

39:27.632 --> 39:29.799
[ ENGINE REVVING ]

39:31.703 --> 39:33.470
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

39:35.173 --> 39:38.475
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

39:41.146 --> 39:43.747
[ SIGHS ]

39:45.183 --> 39:47.183
[ GRUNTS ]

39:47.185 --> 39:49.052
[ SIGHS ]

39:49.054 --> 39:50.720
HE'S NOT HERE.

39:52.657 --> 39:54.491
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

39:54.493 --> 39:56.159
[ ENGINE REVVING ]

39:57.162 --> 39:59.996
I WAS NEVER THERE FOR HIM
BEFORE.

40:01.032 --> 40:03.199
<i> MAYBE I'M NOT JUST BACK</i>
<i> TO SAVE YOU.</i>

40:03.201 --> 40:06.169
<i> THE MEN WHO TOOK DUVAL HAVE</i>
<i> THEIR PHONES TURNED OFF.</i>

40:06.171 --> 40:07.837
YOUR SON COULD BE ANYWHERE.

40:07.839 --> 40:10.840
NO.

40:10.842 --> 40:11.841
NOT ANYWHERE.

40:11.843 --> 40:13.243
[ ENGINE REVVING ]

40:14.279 --> 40:18.281
Duval: [ GRUNTS ]

40:18.283 --> 40:19.416
John: EASY THERE.

40:19.418 --> 40:22.252
[ GRUNTING ]

40:29.961 --> 40:31.261
RAAAAAAH!

40:31.263 --> 40:33.797
WHOA!
[ GRUNTS ]

40:33.799 --> 40:36.966
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

40:36.968 --> 40:38.468
I told you my son
would get you!

40:38.470 --> 40:39.202
[ GUN COCKS ]

40:39.204 --> 40:40.303
[ SCREAMING ]

40:40.305 --> 40:41.271
Duval:
DON'T YOU DO IT! DON'T!
AAH!

40:41.273 --> 40:42.071
DON'T!

40:42.073 --> 40:43.973
[ WHIMPERING ]

40:43.975 --> 40:45.442
HE KILLED YOUR FATHER!

40:45.444 --> 40:48.278
HE WAS GONNA KILL YOU!
HE WAS IN YOUR HOUSE!

40:48.280 --> 40:51.815
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
THEN HE'S MY CASE,

40:51.817 --> 40:54.651
IF I WANT TO BRING
THE REST OF THEM DOWN!

40:57.556 --> 40:58.321
[ GRUNTS ]

41:03.829 --> 41:05.929
PUT YOUR HANDS
BEHIND YOUR HEAD!

41:05.931 --> 41:07.497
AND GET DOWN ON YOUR KNEES.

41:07.499 --> 41:09.899
I'M NOT GONNA DO THAT.

41:09.901 --> 41:12.435
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?!

41:12.437 --> 41:13.770
[ BREATHES HEAVILY ]

41:13.772 --> 41:16.606
WHAT IS YOUR CONNECTION
TO MY FATHER?!

41:16.608 --> 41:19.008
LIKE I SAID...

41:19.010 --> 41:20.844
I DID SOME WORK FOR HIM.

41:20.846 --> 41:23.480
WHAT IF WE TOOK A BLOOD TEST,
YOU AND ME?

41:23.482 --> 41:26.249
WHAT WOULD THAT SHOW?

41:31.490 --> 41:34.090
NOT RIGHT NOW, NO.
I HAVE TO GO.

41:44.836 --> 41:47.604
[ ENGINE REVVING,
TIRES SQUEALING ]

41:47.606 --> 41:49.639
[ SIGHS ]

41:49.641 --> 41:52.108
[ WARBLING ]

41:52.110 --> 41:54.811
[ SIGHS ]

41:54.813 --> 41:56.980
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

41:56.982 --> 41:58.515
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

41:58.517 --> 42:01.818
